article.description: — Saint Thomas' 20 points helped Northern Colorado defeat Idaho 89-68 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Northern Colorado wins 89-68 over Idaho
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- — Saint Thomas' 20 points helped Northern Colorado defeat Idaho 89-68 on Saturday night. Thomas also added 13 rebounds, eight assists, and three steals for the Bears (12-8, 5-2 Big Sky Conference). Dejour Reaves scored 18 points while going 7 of 10 (4 for 5 from 3-point range). Brock Wisne finished 6 of 7 from the field to finish with 13 points. Quinn Denker led the Vandals (7-13, 1-6) in scoring, finishing with 14 points and six assists. Terren Frank added 13 points and two steals for Idaho. In addition, Tyler Linhardt finished with 10 points. The loss was the Vandals' seventh in a row. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
